cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

This paper deals with the formal verification of concurrent programs, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of computer science logic (cs.LO). The paper specifically focuses on Concurrent Kleene Algebra (CKA), which is a framework for reasoning about concurrent programs. This places the paper in the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces pomset automata as an operational model for CKA, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with completeness results, which is a topic that falls under formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
